article.headline: Coppin St. 81, Winston-Salem 56
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Coppin State went on a 21-6 run in the second half and defeated Winston-Salem 81-56 Tuesday night. Tywain McKee scored 20 points for Coppin (1-3), putting up an 8-for-14 shooting performance. Coppin led by only 5 points, 29-24, at halftime. The Eagles' 11-0 stretch capped the scoring outburst, over the first 5:45 of play as the Eagles increased their lead to 50-30. Robert Pressey scored 12 points and grabbed five rebounds for Coppin. Lowen Wray scored a team-high 13 points for Winston-Salem (1-3).
